Furthermore, since the officials ascertained that the registration number had been &quot;duplicated&quot; since it did not coincide with the one shown in the van&#39;s documentation, the arrested person was also charged with the crime of falsifying public documents.
Ertzaintza is continuing the investigation to arrest the second suspect, who managed to escape as already mentioned, and to determine the origin of the seized drugs.
The 28-year-old AAJ prisoner was taken to the police station to carry out the appropriate procedures and be available to the judge in the next few hours.
Actress Heather Locklear arrested for driving under the influence of drugs
Actress Heather Locklear, the Amanda of the popular series Melrose Place, was arrested this weekend in Santa Barbara, California for driving under the influence of drugs.
A witness saw her perform risky maneuvers as she tried to drive her car out of the parking lot in Montecito, a California highway spokesman revealed to People magazine.
The witness specified that around 4.30 pm Locklear &quot;was pushing the accelerator hard, making a lot of noise, and trying to get the car out of the parking space with sudden maneuvers back and forth. Backing up, she passed several times in front of her sunglasses .&quot;
Shortly thereafter, the witness, who apparently did not recognize the actress at first glance, saw that Locklear had stopped on a nearby street and exited the vehicle.
It was this person who alerted 911 because &quot;she was concerned for Locklear&#39;s life.&quot;
When the police patrol arrived, they found the actress sitting inside her vehicle, which was partially blocking the road.
&quot;She looked confused,&quot; which is why officers took her to a drug and alcohol center for testing.
According to a police spokesman, the actress was cooperative and the hypothesis of excessive alcohol was dismissed from the outset, although &quot;according to what the officers initially observed, we believe that Locklear was under the effect of some drug.&quot;
Locklear was arrested on suspicion of driving under the influence of some unspecified substance and was committed to the local jail at around 7pm, to be released hours later.
Two months ago, Locklear was recovered from a specialist clinic in Arizona after being hospitalized following an episode of anxiety and depression.
