It will never disappear, but perhaps it is necessary to think of the &quot;death&quot; of the operating system not as an absolute truth, but a relative one.
What Ballmer said this week backs up that notion.
People pay less and less attention to the operating system, and more and more to the web browser.
You take your computer just to launch Explorer or Firefox - or Chrome - and every day we spend more time surfing the net than in a remote windowed environment.
What are half of the operating system applications for?
