National industrial sales prices in August 2008 increased by 0.1% compared to the previous month, by 12.9% compared to August 2007 - informs the Hungarian Central Statistical Institute.
The prices of export sales of the industry compared to July 2008 were higher by 1.1%, compared to the previous year instead decreased by 3.9%
As a result of the change in domestic and export prices, industrial production costs were 0.7% higher than the previous month and 3.2% higher than a year ago.
Domestic industrial sales prices compared to the previous month increased by only 0.1%.
Domestic sales prices of the processing sector also climbed minimally, 0.1%, compared to July.
The greatest price increase in August 2008 occurred in the leather and shoe processing sector (2.8%), especially bags and belts with 4.6% and shoe production with 2.5% of monthly increase.
The high price level of plastic and chemical raw materials caused a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the products and chemicals sector.
A decrease in prices occurred in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of electrical tools and machinery (0.9%) and to a minimal extent in wood processing (0.1%).
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing have not changed.
In the other sectors of the processing industry there was a price increase of between 0.2 and 0.9%.
In the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector, prices increased in August by 0.3% in national industrial sales, primarily as a result of the dominant effect of the gas price increase carried out by the authorities since 1 July.
Compared in 12 months, considering the national sales of the processing industry sectors, the largest increases were in the petroleum products processing sector (32.4%).
In the sector of manufacturing products deriving from metalworking, the increase in prices was 13.2%, 11% in the context of the production of food, beverages and tobacco representing a decisive weight.
A decrease in prices occurred in the textile sector (2.5%) and in the sectors of production of electrical tools and machinery (0.3%).
In the other sectors of the processing industry the rate of price increases varied from 0.6% to 9.1%.
In total, in the processing industry, prices rose by 10.2% in the past year.
Prices in the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector exceeded last year&#39;s prices by 18.7%.
In domestic sales among industry target groups, the largest monthly price increase occurred in August in industries producing capital goods (0.7%).
In the sectors that produce consumer items, prices increased by 0.3%, in the energy and other utilities sectors, prices did not change compared to those of the previous month.
In August 2008, compared to the same month last year, the largest price increase was observed in the energy sector and later utilities (16.8%).
In the sectors that produce consumer items the increase was 6.8%, for capital goods a decrease of 1.4% was measured.
Prices of industrial export sales calculated in guilders rose by 1.1% in August compared to the previous month, compared with 12 months decreased by 3.9%.
